{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Util/AddRelatedDecl.html#Mathlib.Tactic.addRelatedDecl\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">addRelatedDecl</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">src </span><span class=\"fn\">tgt</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Lean.Name</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ref</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Lean.Syntax</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">attrs</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TSyntax\">Lean.TSyntax</a> <span class=\"fn\">`Mathlib.Tactic.optAttrArg</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">construct</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Lean.Name</a></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">Lean.MetaM</a> (<a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Lean.Name</a></span>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">docstringPrefix?</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a></span> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option.none\">none</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hoverInfo</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool.false\">false</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">Lean.MetaM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A helper function for constructing a related declaration from an existing one.\n\nThis is currently used by the attributes `reassoc` and `elementwise`,\nand has been factored out to avoid code duplication.\nFeel free to add features as needed for other applications.\n\nThis helper:\n* calls `addDeclarationRangesFromSyntax`, so jump-to-definition works,\n* copies the `protected` status of the existing declaration, and\n* supports copying attributes.\n\nArguments:\n* `src : Name` is the existing declaration that we are modifying.\n* `prefix_ : String` will be prepended and `suffix : String` will be appended to `src`\n  to form the name of the new declaration.\n* `ref : Syntax` is the syntax where the user requested the related declaration.\n* `construct value levels : MetaM (Expr × List Name)`\n  given an `Expr.const` referring to the original declaration, and its universe variables,\n  should construct the value of the new declaration,\n  along with the names of its universe variables.\n* `attrs` is the attributes that should be applied to both the new and the original declaration,\n  e.g. in the usage `@[reassoc (attr := simp)]`.\n  We apply it to both declarations, to have the same behavior as `to_additive`, and to shorten some\n  attribute commands. Note that `@[elementwise (attr := simp), reassoc (attr := simp)]` will try\n  to apply `simp` twice to the current declaration, but that causes no issues.\n* `docstringPrefix?` is prepended to the doc-string of `src` to form the doc-string of `tgt`.\n  If it is `none`, only the doc-string of `src` is used.\n* When `hoverInfo := true`, the generated constant will be shown as the hover information on `ref`.\n  Warning: As a result, the original doc-string of `ref` will not be visible,\n  and go-to-def on `ref` will not go to the definition of `ref`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Util/AddRelatedDecl.html#Mathlib.Tactic.addRelatedDecl","kind":"def","line":30,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.addRelatedDecl","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/a3a10db0e9d66acbebf76c5e6a135066525ac900/Mathlib/Util/AddRelatedDecl.lean#L30-L97"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Util/AddRelatedDecl.html#Mathlib.Tactic.elabOptAttrArg\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">elabOptAttrArg</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TSyntax\">Lean.TSyntax</a> <span class=\"fn\">`Mathlib.Tactic.optAttrArg</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">Lean.Elab.TermElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Attributes.html#Lean.Elab.Attribute\">Lean.Elab.Attribute</a>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Elaborate an `(attr := ...)` argument. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Util/AddRelatedDecl.html#Mathlib.Tactic.elabOptAttrArg","kind":"def","line":25,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.elabOptAttrArg","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/a3a10db0e9d66acbebf76c5e6a135066525ac900/Mathlib/Util/AddRelatedDecl.lean#L25-L28"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Util/AddRelatedDecl.html#Mathlib.Tactic.optAttrArg\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">optAttrArg</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"An `(attr := ...)` argument for applying the same attributes to multiple declarations. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Util/AddRelatedDecl.html#Mathlib.Tactic.optAttrArg","kind":"def","line":22,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.optAttrArg","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/a3a10db0e9d66acbebf76c5e6a135066525ac900/Mathlib/Util/AddRelatedDecl.lean#L22-L23"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Init","Lean.Elab.DeclarationRange"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Util.AddRelatedDecl"}